{"sha": "a288a5ea06bc601802e2f1537f883cb9019a2078", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0NzI0NzEyOmEyODhhNWVhMDZiYzYwMTgwMmUyZjE1MzdmODgzY2I5MDE5YTIwNzg=", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Andrew Chin", "email": "achin@eminence32.net", "date": "2020-01-15T17:05:18Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Andrew Chin", "email": "achin@eminence32.net", "date": "2020-01-15T17:05:18Z"}, "message": "Store nightly snapshot in rust-toolchain file, and use it in cargo.sh\n\nThe rust-toolchain file can also store an exact nightly snapshot\n(instead of just \"nightly\"), so we can store whatever snapshot that\nrustc_codegen_cranelift is known to work with.\n\nThis also lets us add a new feature to `cargo.sh` to let it use the\nexact same nightly snapshot as cg_clif.  If there's a nightly compiler\nmismatch, you get a confusing error message like:\n\n    error: couldn't load codegen backend \"librustc_codegen_cranelift.so\":\n    \"librustc_driver-681e2b4f66c73d3e.so: cannot open\n    shared object file: No such file or directory\"\n\nSo doing this automatically in cargo.sh is useful.", "tree": {"sha": "aa285d4f285af6dbb0f7de1a6222cb798f8af294", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/aa285d4f285af6dbb0f7de1a6222cb798f8af294"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/a288a5ea06bc601802e2f1537f883cb9019a2078", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/a288a5ea06bc601802e2f1537f883cb9019a2078", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/a288a5ea06bc601802e2f1537f883cb9019a2078", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/a288a5ea06bc601802e2f1537f883cb9019a2078/comments", "author": {"login": "eminence", "id": 402454, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQwMjQ1NA==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/402454?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/eminence", "html_url"